v0.53 PER-SOURCE MORTALITY BREAKDOWN — 1-YEAR PROBE
====================================================
Date: 2026-04-29
Probe: scripts/_probe_v053_mortality_breakdown.py --years 1
Sim: example_tornionjoki, seed=42 (matches test_latitudinal_smolt_age_gradient)
Window: 2011-04-01 → 2012-03-31 (1 year smoke)
Walltime: ~5 minutes
Source: instrumentation hook in model_environment.py:_do_survival
        + numpy_backend.survival_with_breakdown (new method)

VERDICT: xfail's `mort_high_temp_T*` hypothesis is FALSIFIED.
  high-temp daily survival = 1.000000 in EVERY month.
  At Tornionjoki summer water temps (12-15°C), the T1=28/T9=24 logistic
  is fully inert.

DOMINANT KERNEL KILLER: terrestrial predation (mort_terr_pred_*).

  Summer 2011 (May–Sep, 153 days, ~1300 PARR avg):
    high-temp        : 1.000000   100.00% annualized (inert)
    stranding        : 1.000000   100.00% annualized (inert)
    condition (starv): 0.999268    76.50% annualized
    fish predation   : 0.998269    53.10% annualized
    terr predation   : 0.990054     2.59% annualized  ← DOMINANT

  cum_combined over 153 summer days = 1.49e-01 (14.9% PARR survive
  the kernel alone over one summer).

  Real Tornionjoki Atlantic salmon parr survival ≈ 30-50%/year.
  Implied daily survival for real population: 0.9967 - 0.9981.
  Observed daily kernel survival in summer: 0.990 (3-7× too aggressive).

PER-REACH terr_pred_min FLOORS (configs/example_tornionjoki.yaml):
  Mouth      : 0.97
  Lower      : 0.965
  Middle     : 0.97
  Upper      : 0.96
  BalticCoast: 0.995 (irrelevant — PARR don't go here)
  Floors are inSALMO-template defaults inherited from
  example_a/example_b warm-river calibration. Not Tornionjoki-tuned.

SEASONAL SIGNATURE:
  terr_pred daily survival drops to 0.987-0.992 in May–Sep,
  recovers to 0.997-1.000 in Oct–Apr. Shape is biologically
  correct (avian/mammal foraging seasonality) but magnitude is
  warm-river-tuned. Same shape as the lo_T mortality v0.52.2
  fixed for eggs — fixture-template baked in for the wrong climate.

