==== INTERPRETATION ====
  * high-temp:    inert at subarctic temps (T9=24°C never reached)
  * stranding:    inert (PARR cells have water year-round)
  * condition:    drops in winter (low food → lower body condition →
                  more starvation risk). Modest contributor.
  * fish predation: secondary, ~0.998 daily summer (53% annualized).
                  Driven by warmth on T-axis (T1=6/T9=2 → high at 12-15°C).
  * terr predation: PRIMARY summer killer, 78% summer mortality alone.
                  Driven by warmth-correlated daylight + small parr length
                  on shallow shelter cells. Floor 0.96-0.97 is too low.

==== RECOMMENDED FIX (v0.53.0) ====
Raise per-reach terr_pred_min in configs/example_tornionjoki.yaml from
0.96-0.97 to ~0.998 (matching real Tornionjoki parr survival of 30-50%/yr).
Same shape as v0.52.2's lo_T calibration — fixture-local override of a
template default that was never subarctic-appropriate.

Optionally tune fish_pred_min from 0.95-0.985 to ~0.999 to bring fish
predation in line as well; current ~53% annualized is on the low end of
plausible for Atlantic salmon parr in remote subarctic streams.

Confirmation: 3-year probe (~45 min walltime) running in background to
verify the 2013 natal-cohort summer also shows terr_pred dominance and
that the recommended floors give cumulative survival ~30%/yr.
